Program: Omnibus
Title: The Memoirs of Sayyida Salme
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lq1
Last Broadcast Date: 13 May 1998
'Her memoirs are without parallel in 19th century East African history' The story of Sayyida Salme, born a Muslim princess in Zanzibar who eloped with a trader and lived most of her life as Emily Ruete, a widow with three children in exile in Germany.